8,400 fans — a fifth of the Red Bull Arena’s capacity — for their first game of the season at home to Mainz on September 20. Hertha Berlin said they will allow 4,000 supporters to attend their home opener five days later. Both the German league (DFL) and German FA have announced they are investing “a seven-figure sum” to finance three scientific studies exploring the conditions required for fans to return to games. VANGUARD Bundesliga clubs have continued to lay down the standards for the rest of the world, in terms of financing, structure, sponsorship and followership. May 13, 2018 In "Sports" Bayern Munich could secure an eighth straight Bundesliga title this weekend, but host Borussia Moenchengladbach on Saturday without suspended duo Thomas Mueller and Robert Lewandowski. Bayern will be confirmed champions with a win on Saturday if second-placed Borussia Dortmund lose at relegation-threatened Fortuna Duesseldorf earlier in the day. That scenario… June 12, 2020 In "Sports" Nicole Bartelt has been a loyal fan at all but two of Borussia Dortmund's home matches since 2008, but when the Bundesliga restarted Saturday after a two-month hiatus because of the coronavirus, she was forced to keep away from the stands. Nevertheless, Bartelt, 44, was not complaining that the derby… May 16, 2020 In "Sports"